headlines.description: — James Harden had 20 points, 11 rebounds and 11 assists to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a comfortable 123-111 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden's triple-double leads 76ers to easy win over Pistons

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 27 points, Scottie Barnes had 22 and the Toronto Raptors snapped a three-game losing streak by beating the Portland Trail Blazers 117-105 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers lose 7th straight on road, Raptors win 117-105

headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored 29 points, Buddy Hield had 21 and the Indiana Pacers capped the first half of their regular-season schedule with a 116-111 comeback victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner, Haliburton key Pacers’ 116-111 victory over Hornets

headlines.description: — Brooklyn got another win. Now the Nets have to hope for good news on Kevin Durant.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets top Heat 102-101, lose Durant to right knee injury

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane had 24 points and nine assists, Tyus Jones added 21 points and the Memphis Grizzlies, playing without leading scorer Ja Morant, defeated the Utah Jazz 123-118 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies, without Morant, beat Jazz, extend win streak to 6

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 22 points and Anthony Edwards added 21 as the Minnesota Timberwolves overcame a big early deficit to beat the Houston Rockets 104-96 Sunday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell, Edwards help Timberwolves beat Rockets 104-96

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Dallas Mavericks 120-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33, leads Thunder past Mavericks

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell doesn't have to score 71 points in a game for the Cleveland Cavaliers to be at their best.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Mitchell lead Cavs past banged-up Suns 112-98

headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 30, Hawks rally to beat reeling Clips 112-108
